eye for the law, combined with his background as an award-winning journalist, demystifies a statute that affects all our lives –for good and for ill. While Section 230 may be imperfect and in need of refinement, Kosseff maintains that it is necessary to foster free speech and innovation. For filings from many of the cases discussed in the book and updates about Section 230, visit jeffkosseff.com  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFreedom of speechzUnited States. 0aInternetxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aLiability (Law)zUnited States. 0aWeb sitesxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 4aHistory Of Technology. 4aLegal History & Studies. 4aMedia Studies.  afree speech.  ainternet law.  ainternet.  aonline abuse.  aprivacy.  asection 230.  atrolling.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198040uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150173578340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501735783423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501735783/original  a978-3-11-065198-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles